What a great question! Add your thoughts and suggestions below, too! There’s plenty of great answers to this question! 

There is so much love and clarity by focusing on your present moment, by learning how to accept yourself fully.

The number one thing I try to teach is total self-acceptance without shame. 

There’s 4 days left until my Art Of Letting Go workshop! If you’re ready to feel energetically lighter, register for the private session at IamLettingGo.net

node.text:
I said it once, and ill repeat it: arguing is the lowest form of communication.

What we want is to be heard, to enter safe forms of communication, and to share how we think and feel. We have to let go of arguing and replace it with listening and collaboration.

Arguing as a vessel does not get you there? Unless you get paid to go on TV and argue, there's no reason to use that tactic in real life. Listen all thriugh on this one for some solid techniques and practices.

There's 9 days left until my Art Of Letting Go workshop starts where you'll learn all about “How To Let Go”. Visit the link in my bio or iamlettinggo.net to get your spot! You dont want to miss this workshop. 

#SylvesterMcNutt

node.text:
What a fun chat on identity. Thank you to everyone who joined me live here on Instagram. 

Here’s the structure of the chat: 

• the question I’m curious about answering
• an explanation of lower and higher vibrations
• an explanation of genuine self-compassion
• step one
• step two
• step three
• summary

node.text:
The first step towards letting go is giving up the obsessive chase to be liked, agreed with, accepted, validated. It's fantastic when we find agreement and when we are validated, that is good for everyone. However, we have to make sure we are not self-abandoning for "approval".

That in itself gives you a great deal of freedom and reign to live your most authentic self.

Comment below and let me know what your thoughts are! 

On August 13th, I'm doing an immersive deep dive into the subject of letting go. I'll teach you how to let go and how to enable the peace of mind you deserve. Go to the link in my bio and reserve your spot in "The Art Of Letting Go Workshop."

node.title: Letting Go: Let Go Of Other People's Approval

node.text:
Speak good energy and life into yourself every single day. Always use self-compasdion when you talk about your journey. As a consequence of self-compassion, your vibration will change. As a consequence of a raised vibration, you'll find it easier to set boundaries.

I'm going live tomorrow on Instagram. Send me your questions or topics you’d like me to cover via direct message. Turn on my post notifications, so you don't miss when I go live!

node.title: How Do I Speak Up For Myself

node.text:
This clip is from a mini-episode of the Free Your Energy podcast. Grab it on Spotify or iTunes.

If you enjoy long-form podcasts, you'll love hearing me jam with world-class teachers, storytellers, and people with immense passion.

During the week, I do mini-episodes on different topics that inspire me!  If you NEED more words on overthinking, I have a mini-course called “How To Stop Overthinking.” You can grab that from Sylvestermcnutt.net/courses

I hope you get into the activity, action, and into the mud! It's the only way to create what you're envisioning!

Focusing on what is outside of you is a path to stress, anxiety, confusion, and who knows what else.

I believe in choosing to see where your opportunities are, to see what you can do with what you have • comment below; let me know what your thoughts are below!

node.text:
Your birthday is not just another day. 🎂 

Save this post, and when your day comes around, I hope you ENJOY IT BECAUSE IT’s YOUR DAY!

A little secret about me, it pains me when people don’t celebrate themselves. I even wrote about it in my next book. Celebrating yourself is a self-love practice.

You’re allowed to and should celebrate yourself. You’re worth it! 

Self-Love season is officially here! #SylvesterMcNutt

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by SYLVESTER MCNUTT III on August 23, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says '"Your birthday is not just another day. ay. Be with people who love you, reflect on the last year, and find deep gratitude for where you are in life." sylvester mcnutt'.

Photo by SYLVESTER MCNUTT III on August 23, 2021. May be an image of text that says '"Your birthday is not just another day. I'm so sorry if people didn't celebrate you in your past, but please, use your day to celebrate you in the present. You matter. Your day matters." -sylvester mcnutt'.
Photo shared by SYLVESTER MCNUTT III on August 23, 2021 tagging @madebyhuy. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text:
8.23 has always been great to me! 🎂 🎈 

My biggest learned lesson over the last year is to release the idea of “identity”, and to lean into the present moment and change.

Detaching from identity caused me to grieve, and to accept what is. Life is always a flow and rhythm so you must learn how to move… I’ve learned that security, stability and comfort are fleeting ideas.

My best habit picked up this year is consistent mediation + the sober curious journey.

Adding in meditation daily and dropping alcohol has had some profound consequences. 

Birthdays are not just another day. Celebrate you. Celebrate with your community. Enjoy the day. Your birthday always matters!

I have a big favor to ask. I’m a self-published author and reviews are the lifeblood to my career. If you’ve ordered and read any of my books, could you please leave a review on Amazon for me!? Thank you in advance! DM your review, I’d love to read it!

Lastly, I’m most grateful for my friends and family. I have good people in my life and I’m so thankful that I have the people I have.

Grateful…thankful…excited 💫
📸 : @madebyhuy 
#SylvesterMcNutt

Drop a 💛 if you value and are choosing to honor your boundaries.

“Productivity” Is the language of capitalism; be aware, and use your boundaries where needed. Life is beautiful. Allow yourself to rest, to have balance, to always MAKE time for life!

If boundaries is a pain point for you, I have a bestselling course that teaches step-by-step HOW to establish boundaries in work, relationships, with self and in family. Sign up via the link in my bio and go to “Build Your Boundaries” course, or go to buildyourboundaries.net and sign up there.

We are coming into self-love season in case you didn’t know. Be proud of yourself. 

#SylvesterMcNutt

You are allowed to be proud of your efforts, your trials, & your journey. Take a minute out of your day to stop, breathe find some gratitude within your beautiful journey. You deserve to hear "I'm proud of you." too.'.

Photo shared by SYLVESTER MCNUTT III on August 21, 2021 tagging @sylvestermcnutt. May be an image of text that says '"I hope you can find genuine self- love and self-compassion this weekend you deserve that." -Sylvester McNutt III'.

node.text:
I hope you take the time to appreciate your body, your mind, your soul.

I hope you deeply honor your grief, your trauma, your pain.

I hope you can reflect and find the appropriate silver linings and pieces of motivation.

I hope you take a moment to appreciate your victories, successes, and triumphs.

Above all else, I hope you find self-compassion and give yourself grace.

We are all learning... Free Your Energy 💫 #SylvesterMcNutt

It's okay to release the comparison, the old stories, the pressure to perform. You're a human who is learning and growing, and even though you don't have all the answers, hope you know that no one does. This weekend, hope you find genuine self-love and self-compassion- you deserve that." -Sylvester McNutt III'.

node.text:
Drop a 💛 if you needed to hear these words from @dr.alexandra.solomon 

Listening is one of the most underdeveloped skills we have.

You can listen to over 100+ videos from the nation's most popular professor, Dr. Solomon, on the powerful emotional wellness app Mine’d (the link is in my bio to download - go get the app!) 

My favorite listening phrase is “Tell me more.” A lot of people wait for their turn to talk. I believe in giving people spaces to be heard — that’s how you deepen understanding and connection.

And, when you listen deeply to someone, you create the space for yourself to be heard as well.  Most people will mirror you and listen deeply if you do.

Free Your Energy #SylvesterMcNutt

Respectfully, the most vital energy resides in is our most authentic self.

Your authentic self may not always have the “best” energy, but who says we must always be our “best.” That's a myth. A myth rooted in production culture.

You're a human; you're always allowed to recover, rest and restore.
